{
  "video_id": "h1Yg1rURKR0",
  "title": "Sebastian Deterding: What your designs say about you",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 15651.0,
      "end_time": 18237.0,
      "text": "We are today talking about moral persuasion:"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 18261.0,
      "end_time": 22243.0,
      "text": "What is moral and immoral in trying to change people&#39;s behaviors"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 22267.0,
      "end_time": 24720.0,
      "text": "by using technology and using design?"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 24744.0,
      "end_time": 26576.0,
      "text": "And I don&#39;t know what you expect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 26600.0,
      "end_time": 28553.0,
      "text": "but when I was thinking about that issue,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 28577.0,
      "end_time": 32616.0,
      "text": "I early on realized what I&#39;m not able to give you are answers."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 33203.0,
      "end_time": 35974.0,
      "text": "I&#39;m not able to tell you what is moral or immoral,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 35998.0,
      "end_time": 38544.0,
      "text": "because we&#39;re living in a pluralist society."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 38569.0,
      "end_time": 42811.0,
      "text": "My values can be radically different from your values,"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 42835.0,
      "end_time": 46120.0,
      "text": "which means that what I consider moral or immoral based on that"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 46360.0,
      "end_time": 49648.0,
      "text": "might not necessarily be what you consider moral or immoral."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 50290.0,
      "end_time": 53243.0,
      "text": "But I also realized there is one thing that I could give you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 53267.0,
      "end_time": 55800.0,
      "text": "and that is what this guy behind me gave the world --"
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 55824.0,
      "end_time": 56974.0,
      "text": "Socrates."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 56998.0,
      "end_time": 58393.0,
      "text": "It is questions."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 58417.0,
      "end_time": 61500.0,
      "text": "What I can do and what I would like to do with you"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 61740.0,
      "end_time": 63190.0,
      "text": "is give you, like that initial question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 63430.0,
      "end_time": 66453.0,
      "text": "a set of questions to figure out for yourselves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 66477.0,
      "end_time": 70118.0,
      "text": "layer by layer, like peeling an onion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 70142.0,
      "end_time": 75161.0,
      "text": "getting at the core of what you believe is moral or immoral persuasion."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 75559.0,
      "end_time": 79600.0,
      "text": "And I&#39;d like to do that with a couple of examples of technologies"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 79624.0,
      "end_time": 84604.0,
      "text": "where people have used game elements to get people to do things."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 85343.0,
      "end_time": 88383.0,
      "text": "So it&#39;s at first a very simple, very obvious question"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 88407.0,
      "end_time": 89603.0,
      "text": "I would like to give you:"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 89627.0,
      "end_time": 92314.0,
      "text": "What are your intentions if you are designing something?"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 92668.0,
      "end_time": 96410.0,
      "text": "And obviously, intentions are not the only thing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 96650.0,
      "end_time": 99243.0,
      "text": "so here is another example for one of these applications."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 99267.0,
      "end_time": 102354.0,
      "text": "There are a couple of these kinds of Eco dashboards right now --"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 102378.0,
      "end_time": 103838.0,
      "text": "dashboards built into cars --"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 103862.0,
      "end_time": 106693.0,
      "text": "which try to motivate you to drive more fuel-efficiently."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 106718.0,
      "end_time": 108491.0,
      "text": "This here is Nissan&#39;s MyLeaf,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 108515.0,
      "end_time": 111579.0,
      "text": "where your driving behavior is compared with the driving behavior"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 111603.0,
      "end_time": 112753.0,
      "text": "of other people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 112778.0,
      "end_time": 116550.0,
      "text": "so you can compete for who drives a route the most fuel-efficiently."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 116790.0,
      "end_time": 118556.0,
      "text": "And these things are very effective, it turns out --"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 118580.0,
      "end_time": 122519.0,
      "text": "so effective that they motivate people to engage in unsafe driving behaviors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 122543.0,
      "end_time": 124305.0,
      "text": "like not stopping at a red light,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 124329.0,
      "end_time": 127440.0,
      "text": "because that way you have to stop and restart the engine,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 127680.0,
      "end_time": 129791.0,
      "text": "and that would use quite some fuel, wouldn&#39;t it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 130338.0,
      "end_time": 134747.0,
      "text": "So despite this being a very well-intended application,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 134771.0,
      "end_time": 137146.0,
      "text": "obviously there was a side effect of that."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 137170.0,
      "end_time": 139718.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s another example for one of these side effects."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 139742.0,
      "end_time": 144525.0,
      "text": "Commendable: a site that allows parents to give their kids little badges"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 144550.0,
      "end_time": 147208.0,
      "text": "for doing the things that parents want their kids to do,"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 147232.0,
      "end_time": 148548.0,
      "text": "like tying their shoes."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 148572.0,
      "end_time": 150816.0,
      "text": "And at first that sounds very nice,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 150840.0,
      "end_time": 152990.0,
      "text": "very benign, well-intended."
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 153140.0,
      "end_time": 156784.0,
      "text": "But it turns out, if you look into research on people&#39;s mindset,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 156808.0,
      "end_time": 158295.0,
      "text": "caring about outcomes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 158319.0,
      "end_time": 160910.0,
      "text": "caring about public recognition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 160116.0,
      "end_time": 163977.0,
      "text": "caring about these kinds of public tokens of recognition"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 164100.0,
      "end_time": 165995.0,
      "text": "is not necessarily very helpful"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 166190.0,
      "end_time": 168326.0,
      "text": "for your long-term psychological well-being."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 168350.0,
      "end_time": 171250.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s better if you care about learning something."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 171500.0,
      "end_time": 172955.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s better when you care about yourself"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 172979.0,
      "end_time": 175553.0,
      "text": "than how you appear in front of other people."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 176210.0,
      "end_time": 181610.0,
      "text": "So that kind of motivational tool that is used actually, in and of itself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 181860.0,
      "end_time": 182994.0,
      "text": "has a long-term side effect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 183180.0,
      "end_time": 184828.0,
      "text": "in that every time we use a technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 184852.0,
      "end_time": 188260.0,
      "text": "that uses something like public recognition or status,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 188500.0,
      "end_time": 190426.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re actually positively endorsing this"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 190450.0,
      "end_time": 193859.0,
      "text": "as a good and normal thing to care about --"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 193884.0,
      "end_time": 196748.0,
      "text": "that way, possibly having a detrimental effect"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 196772.0,
      "end_time": 200626.0,
      "text": "on the long-term psychological well-being of ourselves as a culture."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 200651.0,
      "end_time": 203295.0,
      "text": "So that&#39;s a second, very obvious question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 203319.0,
      "end_time": 205630.0,
      "text": "What are the effects of what you&#39;re doing --"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 205654.0,
      "end_time": 209778.0,
      "text": "the effects you&#39;re having with the device, like less fuel,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 209802.0,
      "end_time": 212507.0,
      "text": "as well as the effects of the actual tools you&#39;re using"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 212531.0,
      "end_time": 214205.0,
      "text": "to get people to do things --"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 214229.0,
      "end_time": 215800.0,
      "text": "public recognition?"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 215824.0,
      "end_time": 218745.0,
      "text": "Now is that all -- intention, effect?"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 218769.0,
      "end_time": 221903.0,
      "text": "Well, there are some technologies which obviously combine both."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 221927.0,
      "end_time": 224714.0,
      "text": "Both good long-term and short-term effects"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 224738.0,
      "end_time": 227547.0,
      "text": "and a positive intention like Fred Stutzman&#39;s \"Freedom,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 227571.0,
      "end_time": 229778.0,
      "text": "where the whole point of that application is --"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 229802.0,
      "end_time": 233527.0,
      "text": "well, we&#39;re usually so bombarded with constant requests by other people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 233551.0,
      "end_time": 234707.0,
      "text": "with this device,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 234731.0,
      "end_time": 238210.0,
      "text": "you can shut off the Internet connectivity of your PC of choice"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 238235.0,
      "end_time": 239683.0,
      "text": "for a pre-set amount of time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 239707.0,
      "end_time": 241678.0,
      "text": "to actually get some work done."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 241702.0,
      "end_time": 244853.0,
      "text": "And I think most of us will agree that&#39;s something well-intended,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 244877.0,
      "end_time": 247970.0,
      "text": "and also has good consequences."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 247121.0,
      "end_time": 248767.0,
      "text": "In the words of Michel Foucault,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 248791.0,
      "end_time": 250731.0,
      "text": "it is a \"technology of the self.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 250755.0,
      "end_time": 253591.0,
      "text": "It is a technology that empowers the individual"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 253616.0,
      "end_time": 255431.0,
      "text": "to determine its own life course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 255455.0,
      "end_time": 256974.0,
      "text": "to shape itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 257410.00000000003,
      "end_time": 260394.00000000003,
      "text": "But the problem is, as Foucault points out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 260418.0,
      "end_time": 262203.0,
      "text": "that every technology of the self"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 262227.0,
      "end_time": 265671.0,
      "text": "has a technology of domination as its flip side."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 265696.0,
      "end_time": 270299.0,
      "text": "As you see in today&#39;s modern liberal democracies,"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 270323.0,
      "end_time": 275600.0,
      "text": "the society, the state, not only allows us to determine our self,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 275300.0,
      "end_time": 276181.0,
      "text": "to shape our self,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 276205.0,
      "end_time": 278195.0,
      "text": "it also demands it of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 278220.0,
      "end_time": 280181.0,
      "text": "It demands that we optimize ourselves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 280205.0,
      "end_time": 282440.0,
      "text": "that we control ourselves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 282690.0,
      "end_time": 284780.0,
      "text": "that we self-manage continuously,"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 284804.0,
      "end_time": 288696.0,
      "text": "because that&#39;s the only way in which such a liberal society works."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 288721.0,
      "end_time": 292989.0,
      "text": "These technologies want us to stay in the game"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 293130.0,
      "end_time": 295786.0,
      "text": "that society has devised for us."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 295810.0,
      "end_time": 298970.0,
      "text": "They want us to fit in even better."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 298121.0,
      "end_time": 300698.0,
      "text": "They want us to optimize ourselves to fit in."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 301628.0,
      "end_time": 304707.0,
      "text": "Now, I don&#39;t say that is necessarily a bad thing;"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 305293.0,
      "end_time": 309621.0,
      "text": "I just think that this example points us to a general realization,"
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 309645.0,
      "end_time": 313448.0,
      "text": "and that is: no matter what technology or design you look at,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 313472.0,
      "end_time": 316493.0,
      "text": "even something we consider as well-intended"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 316517.0,
      "end_time": 319483.0,
      "text": "and as good in its effects as Stutzman&#39;s Freedom,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 319507.0,
      "end_time": 322214.0,
      "text": "comes with certain values embedded in it."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 322238.0,
      "end_time": 324174.0,
      "text": "And we can question these values."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 324198.0,
      "end_time": 326142.0,
      "text": "We can question: Is it a good thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 326166.0,
      "end_time": 329650.0,
      "text": "that all of us continuously self-optimize ourselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 329674.0,
      "end_time": 331685.0,
      "text": "to fit better into that society?"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 331709.0,
      "end_time": 333201.0,
      "text": "Or to give you another example:"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 333225.0,
      "end_time": 335701.0,
      "text": "What about a piece of persuasive technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 335725.0,
      "end_time": 338916.0,
      "text": "that convinces Muslim women to wear their headscarves?"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 338940.0,
      "end_time": 340992.0,
      "text": "Is that a good or a bad technology"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 341160.0,
      "end_time": 343579.0,
      "text": "in its intentions or in its effects?"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 343603.0,
      "end_time": 347857.0,
      "text": "Well, that basically depends on the kind of values you bring to bear"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 347881.0,
      "end_time": 350118.0,
      "text": "to make these kinds of judgments."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 350142.0,
      "end_time": 351670.0,
      "text": "So that&#39;s a third question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 351694.0,
      "end_time": 353222.0,
      "text": "What values do you use to judge?"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 353848.0,
      "end_time": 355189.0,
      "text": "And speaking of values:"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 355213.0,
      "end_time": 358569.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve noticed that in the discussion about moral persuasion online"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 358593.0,
      "end_time": 360230.0,
      "text": "and when I&#39;m talking with people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 360254.0,
      "end_time": 362921.0,
      "text": "more often than not, there is a weird bias."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 363463.0,
      "end_time": 366359.0,
      "text": "And that bias is that we&#39;re asking:"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 366383.0,
      "end_time": 369195.0,
      "text": "Is this or that \"still\" ethical?"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 369220.0,
      "end_time": 371870.0,
      "text": "Is it \"still\" permissible?"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 371894.0,
      "end_time": 373920.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re asking things like:"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 373116.0,
      "end_time": 375305.0,
      "text": "Is this Oxfam donation form,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 375329.0,
      "end_time": 378377.0,
      "text": "where the regular monthly donation is the preset default,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 378401.0,
      "end_time": 380480.0,
      "text": "and people, maybe without intending it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 380504.0,
      "end_time": 384316.0,
      "text": "are encouraged or nudged into giving a regular donation"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 384340.0,
      "end_time": 385828.0,
      "text": "instead of a one-time donation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 385853.0,
      "end_time": 387196.0,
      "text": "is that \"still&#39; permissible?"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 387220.0,
      "end_time": 388583.0,
      "text": "Is it \"still\" ethical?"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 388607.0,
      "end_time": 390860.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re fishing at the low end."
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 390879.0,
      "end_time": 393353.0,
      "text": "But in fact, that question, \"Is it &#39;still&#39; ethical?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 393377.0,
      "end_time": 395158.0,
      "text": "is just one way of looking at ethics."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 395182.0,
      "end_time": 400740.0,
      "text": "Because if you look at the beginning of ethics in Western culture,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 400980.0,
      "end_time": 403630.0,
      "text": "you see a very different idea of what ethics also could be."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 403970.0,
      "end_time": 407967.0,
      "text": "For Aristotle, ethics was not about the question,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 407991.0,
      "end_time": 410263.0,
      "text": "\"Is that still good, or is it bad?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 410287.0,
      "end_time": 413715.0,
      "text": "Ethics was about the question of how to live life well."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 414216.0,
      "end_time": 416397.0,
      "text": "And he put that in the word \"arête,\""
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 416421.0,
      "end_time": 419176.0,
      "text": "which we, from [Ancient Greek], translate as \"virtue.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 419200.0,
      "end_time": 420840.0,
      "text": "But really, it means \"excellence.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 420864.0,
      "end_time": 426294.0,
      "text": "It means living up to your own full potential as a human being."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 426937.0,
      "end_time": 428593.0,
      "text": "And that is an idea that, I think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 428617.0,
      "end_time": 431314.0,
      "text": "Paul Richard Buchanan put nicely in a recent essay,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 431338.0,
      "end_time": 433481.0,
      "text": "where he said, \"Products are vivid arguments"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 433505.0,
      "end_time": 435628.0,
      "text": "about how we should live our lives.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 436860.0,
      "end_time": 438663.0,
      "text": "Our designs are not ethical or unethical"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 438687.0,
      "end_time": 443277.0,
      "text": "in that they&#39;re using ethical or unethical means of persuading us."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 443661.0,
      "end_time": 445231.0,
      "text": "They have a moral component"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 445255.0,
      "end_time": 449482.0,
      "text": "just in the kind of vision and the aspiration of the good life"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 449506.0,
      "end_time": 450854.0,
      "text": "that they present to us."
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 451441.0,
      "end_time": 454943.0,
      "text": "And if you look into the designed environment around us"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 454968.0,
      "end_time": 456140.0,
      "text": "with that kind of lens,"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 456164.0,
      "end_time": 458616.0,
      "text": "asking, \"What is the vision of the good life"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 458641.0,
      "end_time": 461379.0,
      "text": "that our products, our design, present to us?\","
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 461403.0,
      "end_time": 463679.0,
      "text": "then you often get the shivers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 463703.0,
      "end_time": 466300.0,
      "text": "because of how little we expect of each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 466550.0,
      "end_time": 469945.0,
      "text": "of how little we actually seem to expect of our life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 469969.0,
      "end_time": 472300.0,
      "text": "and what the good life looks like."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 473110.0,
      "end_time": 476133.0,
      "text": "So that&#39;s a fourth question I&#39;d like to leave you with:"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 476157.0,
      "end_time": 480519.0,
      "text": "What vision of the good life do your designs convey?"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 481249.0,
      "end_time": 482621.0,
      "text": "And speaking of design,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 482645.0,
      "end_time": 486835.0,
      "text": "you&#39;ll notice that I already broadened the discussion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 486859.0,
      "end_time": 491303.0,
      "text": "because it&#39;s not just persuasive technology that we&#39;re talking about here,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 491327.0,
      "end_time": 495404.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s any piece of design that we put out here in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 495428.0,
      "end_time": 496828.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t know whether you know"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 496852.0,
      "end_time": 500407.0,
      "text": "the great communication researcher Paul Watzlawick who, back in the &#39;60s,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 500431.0,
      "end_time": 502942.0,
      "text": "made the argument that we cannot not communicate."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 502966.0,
      "end_time": 505567.0,
      "text": "Even if we choose to be silent, we chose to be silent,"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 505591.0,
      "end_time": 508547.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re communicating something by choosing to be silent."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 508571.0,
      "end_time": 511306.0,
      "text": "And in the same way that we cannot not communicate,"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 511330.0,
      "end_time": 512861.0,
      "text": "we cannot not persuade:"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 512885.0,
      "end_time": 514895.0,
      "text": "whatever we do or refrain from doing,"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 514919.0,
      "end_time": 519284.0,
      "text": "whatever we put out there as a piece of design, into the world,"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 519308.0,
      "end_time": 521356.0,
      "text": "has a persuasive component."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 521380.0,
      "end_time": 523253.0,
      "text": "It tries to affect people."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 523277.00000000006,
      "end_time": 527240.0,
      "text": "It puts a certain vision of the good life out there in front of us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 527480.0,
      "end_time": 528673.0,
      "text": "which is what Peter-Paul Verbeek,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 528697.0,
      "end_time": 531413.0,
      "text": "the Dutch philosopher of technology, says."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 531437.0,
      "end_time": 535385.0,
      "text": "No matter whether we as designers intend it or not,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 535409.0,
      "end_time": 537551.0,
      "text": "we materialize morality."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 537575.0,
      "end_time": 540378.0,
      "text": "We make certain things harder and easier to do."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 540402.0,
      "end_time": 542613.0,
      "text": "We organize the existence of people."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 542637.0,
      "end_time": 543787.0,
      "text": "We put a certain vision"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 543812.0,
      "end_time": 547216.0,
      "text": "of what good or bad or normal or usual is"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 547240.0,
      "end_time": 548391.0,
      "text": "in front of people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 548415.0,
      "end_time": 550814.0,
      "text": "by everything we put out there in the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 551247.0,
      "end_time": 554333.0,
      "text": "Even something as innocuous as a set of school chairs"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 554357.0,
      "end_time": 556404.0,
      "text": "is a persuasive technology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 556428.0,
      "end_time": 561118.0,
      "text": "because it presents and materializes a certain vision of the good life --"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 561142.0,
      "end_time": 563999.0,
      "text": "a good life in which teaching and learning and listening"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 564230.0,
      "end_time": 567122.0,
      "text": "is about one person teaching, the others listening;"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 567146.0,
      "end_time": 571199.0,
      "text": "in which it is about learning-is-done-while-sitting;"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 571223.0,
      "end_time": 572818.0,
      "text": "in which you learn for yourself;"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 572842.0,
      "end_time": 575262.0,
      "text": "in which you&#39;re not supposed to change these rules,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 575286.0,
      "end_time": 577733.0,
      "text": "because the chairs are fixed to the ground."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 578888.0,
      "end_time": 581799.0,
      "text": "And even something as innocuous as a single-design chair,"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 581823.0,
      "end_time": 583395.0,
      "text": "like this one by Arne Jacobsen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 583419.0,
      "end_time": 585194.0,
      "text": "is a persuasive technology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 585219.0,
      "end_time": 588262.0,
      "text": "because, again, it communicates an idea of the good life:"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 588735.0,
      "end_time": 593660.0,
      "text": "a good life -- a life that you, as a designer, consent to by saying,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 593684.0,
      "end_time": 597190.0,
      "text": "\"In a good life, goods are produced as sustainably or unsustainably"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 597215.0,
      "end_time": 598826.0,
      "text": "as this chair."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 598850.0,
      "end_time": 600827.0,
      "text": "Workers are treated as well or as badly"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 600851.0,
      "end_time": 603423.0,
      "text": "as the workers were treated that built that chair.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 603762.0,
      "end_time": 606630.0,
      "text": "The good life is a life where design is important"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 606870.0,
      "end_time": 609800.0,
      "text": "because somebody obviously took the time and spent the money"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 609320.0,
      "end_time": 610816.0,
      "text": "for that kind of well-designed chair;"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 610840.0,
      "end_time": 612244.0,
      "text": "where tradition is important,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 612268.0,
      "end_time": 615434.0,
      "text": "because this is a traditional classic and someone cared about this;"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 615458.0,
      "end_time": 618148.0,
      "text": "and where there is something as conspicuous consumption,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 618172.0,
      "end_time": 621128.0,
      "text": "where it is OK and normal to spend a humongous amount of money"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 621152.0,
      "end_time": 622303.0,
      "text": "on such a chair,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 622327.0,
      "end_time": 624900.0,
      "text": "to signal to other people what your social status is."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 624924.0,
      "end_time": 628241.0,
      "text": "So these are the kinds of layers, the kinds of questions"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 628265.0,
      "end_time": 630235.0,
      "text": "I wanted to lead you through today;"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 630259.0,
      "end_time": 633293.0,
      "text": "the question of: What are the intentions that you bring to bear"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 633317.0,
      "end_time": 634877.0,
      "text": "when you&#39;re designing something?"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 634901.0,
      "end_time": 638152.0,
      "text": "What are the effects, intended and unintended, that you&#39;re having?"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 638177.0,
      "end_time": 640978.0,
      "text": "What are the values you&#39;re using to judge those?"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 641200.0,
      "end_time": 642974.0,
      "text": "What are the virtues, the aspirations"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 642999.0,
      "end_time": 645270.0,
      "text": "that you&#39;re actually expressing in that?"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 645400.0,
      "end_time": 647257.0,
      "text": "And how does that apply,"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 647281.0,
      "end_time": 649266.0,
      "text": "not just to persuasive technology,"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 649291.0,
      "end_time": 651339.0,
      "text": "but to everything you design?"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 651912.0,
      "end_time": 653203.0,
      "text": "Do we stop there?"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 653815.0,
      "end_time": 654982.0,
      "text": "I don&#39;t think so."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 655291.0,
      "end_time": 659729.0,
      "text": "I think that all of these things are eventually informed"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 659753.0,
      "end_time": 661176.0,
      "text": "by the core of all of this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 661200.0,
      "end_time": 664291.0,
      "text": "and this is nothing but life itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 664594.0,
      "end_time": 667311.0,
      "text": "Why, when the question of what the good life is"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 667335.0,
      "end_time": 669674.0,
      "text": "informs everything that we design,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 669698.0,
      "end_time": 672492.0,
      "text": "should we stop at design and not ask ourselves:"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 672516.0,
      "end_time": 674506.0,
      "text": "How does it apply to our own life?"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 674881.0,
      "end_time": 677593.0,
      "text": "\"Why should the lamp or the house be an art object,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 677617.0,
      "end_time": 678793.0,
      "text": "but not our life?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 678817.0,
      "end_time": 680300.0,
      "text": "as Michel Foucault puts it."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 680696.0,
      "end_time": 684307.0,
      "text": "Just to give you a practical example of Buster Benson."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 684331.0,
      "end_time": 686589.0,
      "text": "This is Buster setting up a pull-up machine"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 686613.0,
      "end_time": 689225.0,
      "text": "at the office of his new start-up, Habit Labs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 689249.0,
      "end_time": 692464.0,
      "text": "where they&#39;re trying to build other applications like \"Health Month\""
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 692488.0,
      "end_time": 693646.0,
      "text": "for people."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 693670.0,
      "end_time": 695632.0,
      "text": "And why is he building a thing like this?"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 695656.0,
      "end_time": 697689.0,
      "text": "Well, here is the set of axioms"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 697713.0,
      "end_time": 701111.0,
      "text": "that Habit Labs, Buster&#39;s start-up, put up for themselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 701135.0,
      "end_time": 703840.0,
      "text": "on how they wanted to work together as a team"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 703864.0,
      "end_time": 705893.0,
      "text": "when they&#39;re building these applications --"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 705917.0,
      "end_time": 708106.0,
      "text": "a set of moral principles they set themselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 708130.0,
      "end_time": 709491.0,
      "text": "for working together --"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 709515.0,
      "end_time": 710753.0,
      "text": "one of them being,"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 710777.0,
      "end_time": 713864.0,
      "text": "\"We take care of our own health and manage our own burnout.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 714221.0,
      "end_time": 717721.0,
      "text": "Because ultimately, how can you ask yourselves"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 717745.0,
      "end_time": 721675.0,
      "text": "and how can you find an answer on what vision of the good life"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 721699.0,
      "end_time": 724867.0,
      "text": "you want to convey and create with your designs"
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 724892.0,
      "end_time": 726622.0,
      "text": "without asking the question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 726646.0,
      "end_time": 730478.0,
      "text": "What vision of the good life do you yourself want to live?"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 731180.0,
      "end_time": 732192.0,
      "text": "And with that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 732945.0,
      "end_time": 734357.0,
      "text": "I thank you."
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 734381.0,
      "end_time": 738536.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}